Working with strings
    Definition:
      - This is the most used data type through our php apps
    
    Functions:
      strtolower()  =>This funcion takes a string and converts to lowercase
      strtoupper()  => converts to lowercase
      strlen()      => String length
      str_replace(substrNew, substrOld, string) => Return a new string with replacements
      substr(string, startIndx, #characters) 
      ...
      ...

    Index sting:
      - We can index a specific character of our string just using square brackets
       e.g $phrase[0] => get 1st character of our string
           $phrase[1] => get 2nd character of our string
    
-- site.php
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Document</title>
</head>
<body>
    <?php 
        $phrase = "this is my logo";
        str_replace("this", "This", $phrase);
        echo strtolower($phrase);
        echo strlen($phrase);
        echo $phrase[1];
        
    ?>
</body>
</html>